      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-4 mb-6">How to Build a Mobile App for Your Spryker Site (The Smart Way)</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 mb-8">Want to level up engagement, retention, and long-term revenue? Build a mobile app. This article shows you how easy it is to turn your Spryker website into full-featured mobile apps, with MobiLoud.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-slate-50">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose prose-lg prose-slate">
      <p id="">If you're running your ecommerce site on Spryker, that means you understand the value of a custom, high-performance tech stack.</p><p id="">Now, you’re looking to take the next step and launch a mobile app. It’s a logical move — mobile apps are the single most powerful channel for driving retention and increasing customer lifetime value.</p><p id="">Your most loyal customers <em id="">want</em> an app. It offers a more convenient, focused, and personal shopping experience.</p><p id="">But for a brand on a platform as specialized as Spryker, the path to a mobile app can seem daunting. How do you translate the power and complexity of your custom-built Spryker site into a high-quality mobile app without a massive, budget-draining project?</p><p id="">This article will show you how. We’ll explore why traditional app development is a challenge for Spryker users and reveal a smarter, faster, and more cost-effective solution that aligns perfectly with the Spryker philosophy.</p><h2 id="">The Challenge: Why Building an App for Spryker is Inherently Difficult</h2><p id="">Spryker is not like Shopify or other template-based platforms. Its strength lies in its headless, API-first architecture.</p><p id="">This composable commerce model gives you the freedom to build exactly the customer experience you want, connecting any frontend, third-party tool, or touchpoint.</p><p id="">While Spryker provides the powerful Glue API to connect a mobile app, it does not offer a simple, out-of-the-box app builder.</p><p id="">This is by design; the platform is built for custom solutions, not one-size-fits-all templates.</p><p id="">This leaves Spryker users facing a difficult choice, often leading them down the path of full native app development. This involves:</p><ul id=""><li id=""><strong id="">Building from Scratch:</strong> Your development team would need to build separate apps for iOS (using Swift or Objective-C) and Android (using Kotlin or Java), or use a cross-platform framework like React Native.</li><li id=""><strong id="">High Costs:</strong> A custom native app project is a significant investment. Agencies can charge well over <strong id="">$100,000</strong> for the first version alone, and internal costs for a dedicated mobile team are even higher.</li><li id=""><strong id="">Long Timelines:</strong> Developing, testing, and launching a custom app can take anywhere from 6 to 12 months, if not longer.</li><li id=""><strong id="">Duplicated Effort:</strong> You are essentially rebuilding your entire frontend. All the logic, features, and integrations you’ve perfected on your Spryker site must be recreated for the app. This creates a second codebase that needs to be managed, updated, and maintained separately from your website, creating a huge operational drag.</li></ul><p id="">This traditional approach seems to contradict the very reason many brands choose Spryker in the first place.</p><h2 id="">The Spryker Philosophy Meets its Perfect Match</h2><p id="">Spryker’s homepage states the following:</p><blockquote id=""><strong id="">Build Faster. Lower Your IT Costs.</strong><br>When you want more than your standard platform can deliver, but your CFO wants you to save costs.</blockquote><figure class="w-richtext-figure-type-image w-richtext-align-fullwidth" style="max-width:1876px" data-rt-type="image" data-rt-align="fullwidth" data-rt-max-width="1876px"><div><img src="https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63894f0e251e567f6e443bfa/691d8fe954d5eefc1cb62f7c_Digital-Commerce-Platform-for-B2B-B2C-Marketplace-Spryker.webp" loading="lazy" alt="__wf_reserved_inherit"></div></figure><p id="">This is the core dilemma for ambitious ecommerce brands: how to achieve a superior, custom experience without the associated costs and complexity.</p><p id="">The traditional route of building a native app directly conflicts with this goal. You want <em id="">more</em> than a generic app, but you don’t want to drain your IT budget and distract your team for the next year.</p><p id="">This is where MobiLoud comes in. MobiLoud is a full-service solution that was built to solve this exact problem, especially for brands on custom, headless, or niche platforms like Spryker.&nbsp;</p><figure id="" class="w-richtext-figure-type-image w-richtext-align-fullwidth" style="max-width:2240px" data-rt-type="image" data-rt-align="fullwidth" data-rt-max-width="2240px"><div id=""><img src="https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63894f0e251e567f6e443bfa/6865a4f4056b4606aecd61ef_20250702T0915-19da40c7-e172-4f2e-9c52-6b85a200c19a.webp" loading="lazy" alt="__wf_reserved_inherit" width="auto" height="auto" id=""></div><figcaption id="">A few examples of apps we've built for successful brands.&nbsp;Check out more examples <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/examples" id="">here</a></figcaption></figure><p id="">It offers a “third way” that aligns perfectly with the Spryker philosophy: get the high-quality, custom app you want, but do it faster and at a fraction of the cost.</p><h2 id="">What is MobiLoud and Why is it Ideal for Spryker?</h2><p id="">MobiLoud is not another restrictive, template-based app builder. It’s a fully managed service that converts your existing, high-performance Spryker website into premium native mobile apps for iOS and Android.</p><p id="">Here’s how it works:</p><p id="">MobiLoud uses a sophisticated and perfected hybrid app approach.</p><p id="">Your existing Spryker site, with all its custom features, complex logic, and third-party integrations, is the core of your app.</p><p id="">Our platform then layers on native mobile UI elements, such as a native tab menu, navigation, splash screens, and settings.</p><p id="">Crucially, our team of experts handles the entire process for you. This includes initial configuration, design tweaks to optimize the mobile experience, publishing to the App Store and Google Play, and all ongoing technical maintenance and updates.</p><figure id="" class="w-richtext-figure-type-image w-richtext-align-fullwidth" style="max-width:819px" data-rt-type="image" data-rt-align="fullwidth" data-rt-max-width="819px"><div id=""><img src="https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63894f0e251e567f6e443bfa/67075e2f0cef346a43f19076_67075e2a19ccf129272c8b75_670595a58cd21d6631596ce2_jv-app-stores.avif" loading="lazy" alt="__wf_reserved_inherit" width="auto" height="auto" id=""></div><figcaption id="">MobiLoud puts your brand in the App Stores, and in your customer's pocket</figcaption></figure><p id="">This approach is the ideal solution for Spryker brands for several key reasons:</p><div data-rt-embed-type='true'><div style="overflow-x: auto; margin: 2em 0;">
